<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
  <title>Test an inline absolute is positioned after trailing whitespace is trimmed</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Mike Bremford" href="http://bfo.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#absolute-positioning"/>
  <link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-text-3/#text-encoding"/>
  <link rel="match" href="../../reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square-only.html"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="ahem" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../../../fonts/ahem.css"/>
  <meta name="assert" contents="The static position of an inline absolute should reflect any trailing whitespace that needs to be trimmed"/>
  <style>
   .block {
       font: 50px/1 Ahem;
       color: green;
   }
   .pos {
       display: inline;
       position: absolute;
   }
  </style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square.</p>
  <div class="block">
   A <div class="pos">A</div><br/>
   AA
  </div>
 </body>
</html>
